Project Name: McDonald's Web App Project

Introduction
This is a web application that emulates the user interface and functionality of McDonald's website. 
The application is built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript programming languages with the help of the 
Bootstrap framework.

Features
The McDonald's web app has the following features:

A navigation bar with the McDonald's logo and four navigation links (Home, About, Services, and Contact)
A search box with a Go button, and an appended background image in the header section
Eight product cards displaying the images and names of McDonald's meals and burgers
Card hover effect, where the card color fades and the image zooms in
Clicking on a card takes the user to a new page, burger.html, where the selected product's information is displayed
The burger.html page shows the selected product's image, name, a paragraph for the card, a list of ingredients, and 
nutrition summary
An "Add+" button is present on the card, which adds the selected product to the cart and displays the purchase summary, 
including the product's price and GST
A footer with company information and social media links

Installation
To run this project, clone the repository using the following command:
git clone 


Then, open the index.html file in your preferred web browser to view the application.

Usage
The McDonald's web app is designed to mimic the functionality and user experience of the McDonald's website. Users 
can navigate to different sections of the site using the navigation bar, add items to the cart by clicking on the product card. 
